-- Brazilian Stock Movers: Bradesco, HRT, Itau Tumble; OGX Advances
-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 2012-01-30T13:51:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/brazilian-stock-movers-bradesco-hrt-itau-tumble-ogx-advances.html
The following companies are having
 unusual  price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:48 a.m. local time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  Index declined 1.2 percent to 62,161.96.  Banco Bradesco SA (BBDC4)  (BBDC4 BS) fell 2.2 percent to 32.24
reais, and  Itau Unibanco Holding SA (ITUB4)  (ITUB4 BS) dropped 2 percent
to 35.39 reais. Each was cut to “neutral” from “overweight”
at JPMorgan Chase & Co.  HRT Participacoes em Petroleo SA  (HRTP3 BS) slid 1.7
percent to 452.30 reais. The Brazilian oil and gas company was
lowered to “sell” from “buy” at UBS AG after Russia’s TNK-BP
reduced its commitment to invest in a joint venture in the
Amazon.  OGX Petroleo & Gas Participacoes SA  (OGXP3 BS) climbed 0.3
percent to 16.10 reais. The  oil company  controlled by
billionaire  Eike Batista  said in a statement on its website it
began procedures on Jan. 28 to produce its first oil from an
offshore well in  Brazil .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in  Sao Paulo  at 
 ncruz4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos in New York at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  